Silke Helfrich:

""Pool & Share" approach goes beyond equivalence exchange: you pool sth to support a project, make co-use of or simply share it, but you don't pool & share only the resources (f.i. money/ skills/ data-space) but also the risk. This way you decouple giving and taking; and still have access to the benefits - sometimes immediately, sometimes later, sometimes never if you don't need it or consider your contribution a gif etc... "


